Step 3: Grant GitHub Action Permissions (Crucial 🔑)
By default, GitHub blocks Actions from pushing code back into your repo. You must unlock this on the GitHub Web interface:

Open your repository page on GitHub.
Click on Settings (the gear icon on the top tab bar).
On the left sidebar, click Actions → General.
Scroll down to the bottom section called Workflow permissions.
Switch the radio button to Read and write permissions.Click the Save button.
